Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic properties of aqueous 4-hydroxyproline at different temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: Specific heat capacities (cp) and apparent molar heat capacities (Cp,2,phi) of aqueous 4-hydroxyproline have  been measured from T = (298.15 to 328.15) K over the molality range of (0.101708 to  2.031524) mol kg-1 using micro differential scanning calorimetry. The values of density (q), apparent  molar volume (V2,phi), speed of sound (u), and adiabatic apparent molar compressibility (KS,2,phi) have also  been determined for aqueous 4-hydroxyproline from T = (288.15 to 313.15) K over the molality range  of (0.037934 to 0.786476) mol kg-1. The results of these measurements have been used to calculate  nine standard partial molar quantities and their temperature derivatives for aqueous 4-hydroxyproline  as a function of temperature. Isothermal titration calorimetry has been used  to determine the heat of dilution (q) of aqueous 4-hydroxyproline and aqueous L-proline in water over  the temperature range from (288.15 to 308.15) K. The results have been discussed in terms of the changes  in interactions of 4-hydroxyproline and L-proline molecules in the aqueous form, and their water structure  promoting ability with rise in temperature.
